          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1618243962913-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your<strong> cannellini beans</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> drained cannellini beans </strong>to the pot with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – these are your <strong>homemade beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707820911180-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1707820911180-x400.jpg",
